But the action returns the desired value. I'm running a simple nodejs action shown above
```
/**
 * Hello world as an OpenWhisk action.
 */
function main(params) {
    var name = params.name || 'World';
    return {payload:  'Hello, ' + name + '!'};
}
```

Do you know a way to verify what is going wrong?

@marcelfvieira 
IIRC, the invoker directly accesses the container log in the host path.
If the path is not accessible from the inside of the invoker container, I think the error would happen.

